title: Veeam Backup Tasks (Per-VM Details)
agents: veeam_rest
catalog: app/veeam
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors individual Veeam backup task sessions via the REST API.

 Each task represents a VM or object being backed up, providing detailed
 performance metrics including:
 - Backup duration
 - Data processed, read, and transferred
 - Processing speed and bottleneck information
 - Backup age

 The check returns:
 - OK: Backup completed successfully
 - WARN: Backup completed with warnings, or exceeded age/duration thresholds
 - CRIT: Backup failed
 - UNKNOWN: No data or task not found

 This check replaces the veeam_client section from the PowerShell plugin.

item:
 The object name (VM, file share, etc.)

discovery:
 One service is created for each unique backup object.
